JOHANNESBURG - Music legend Johnny Clegg is hanging up his microphone and saying goodbye to the stage. READ: Johnny Clegg bids fans goodbye His Farewell Journey Tour is in full swing and he was joined on stage, in Johannesburg, by The Soweto Gospel Choir, the Parlotones and his son, Jesse.  The guest performers also included Arno Carstens. Concert attendees called the performance "absolutely amazing" and expressed sadness at the news of Clegg's retirement.
	
